cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.SC. 

The paper deals with the computation of polynomial invariants for affine programs, which involves algebraic and semigroup computations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), which deals with mathematical logic and its applications in computer science. The paper also involves computations with polynomials and matrices, which are relevant to the categories cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of semigroups suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), while the algebraic result of independent interest may also place the paper in the category cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
